artworks.title: AKA-ZONAE

creator.name: hiyoko-shisho
creator.description: Japanese VR artist, born in 1987.He had never drawn before, but after encountering VR art in November 2019, he taught himself the technique. He is determined to draw VR art until he dies in order to materialize the world inside of him.

artworks.description: I created a samurai robot based on the motif of AKA-ZONAE(red-armor).The AKA-ZONAE was an actual military formation during the Warring States period in Japan, and was often an elite unit led by a military commander who excelled in bravery, and was passed down to future generations as a symbol of the honor of bravery.

artworks.title: Entity's Latent Space Craft

creator.name: Bård Ionson
creator.description: An artist exploring the distortions between realities using old & new technology. He has exhibited art in Dubai, Italy, Paris, New York, Denver, Berlin, Washington DC and everywhere on the blockchain. This art includes 3D, projection mapping and augmented reality pieces using oscilloscopes, scanners and artificial intelligence.

artworks.description: The Entity travels through time in this latent space craft. They are from the far future from what used to be earth. They have evolved the ability to travel through our ancient computer networks. This is one representation of The Entity they have adopted based on their study of human documentaries on alien life. Is The Entity friendly or hostile to the humans? sageAnomaly.com

artworks.title: Pachamama

creator.name: Metatronix
creator.description: Metatronix, AKA Angelea Torralva, is a multifaceted self taught artist from Grand Rapids, Michigan. Art in all forms has always been her passion. Torralva started her live painting journey in 2013, painting at all kinds of EDM and DNB events/festivals, which has also included live body painting. Torralva is an established artist in Grand Rapids, Michigan and has had solo and group art shows, as well as an AR/VR exhibit in LA, California. Virtual and augmented reality is her current venture as she hopes to create more immersive and live experiences.

artworks.description: A depiction of the Goddess, Pachamama, or Mother Earth. She is an Incan deity who presides over planting and harvesting, represents fertility, embodies the mountains and causes earthquakes.
